15/09/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The leader of the main opposition party New Democracy (ND), Costas Karamanlis, outlined priorities on Saturday (13 September), in light of the general elections next spring. 
ND's goal would be development and prosperity everywhere in the country, Karamanlis said. 
He pledged to reduce defence spending in favour of social funding and to strengthen co-operation with neighbouring countries. 
(ANA, MPA - 14/09/03)
